race.description: Fleurieu Community Bendigo Bank Maiden Plate
race.comment: UPTOWN MONK (9) was well supported on debut in town but simply left himself with too much to do before launching late into fourth. With the benefit of race experience he'll be very hard to hold out. CAUSEWELUVADELAIDE (10) made a bright return here on Feb 1, sticking on gamely to miss by only a long neck. He'll tighten up from that and draws to get every favour. ELITE THUNDER (2) was a flashing light late when resuming in town, charging home into a midfield finish at big odds. He's fitter now, draws the inside, and Toeroek sticking is a strong lead. Right in the mix. NO BAIL (6) is a Press Statement gelding on debut for the Blanch yard who has shown plenty in his jumpouts. A forward showing won't surprise.
